		<h1 class="headings shadow">Testing</h1>
		<p class="p-justified">I’m pretty sure I use Chrome’s DOM more often than my text editor when writing code. 80% of writing code is testing and fixing bugs. For smaller projects, the DOM is your best friend. For larger undertakings that will have many iterations, a testing framework (like Mocha) is an indispensable tool. It would be mortifying for your users to discover a bug you’ve overlooked. Right?</p>		
