	<h1 class="headings shadow">Culture</h1>
	<h1 class="headings shadow">Fit</h1>
	<p class="p-left">Why can’t we all just get along? Well, because we’re not the same person with the same history. We are diverse and that’s a really good thing more than it is a pain. I remind myself of this when I need to tolerate difficult personalities. And what if I’m the difficult personality that others are tolerating? I try to minimize friction by modeling the behavior I want to experience from others. These would be: Directness tempered by kindness and perspective. Embracing teamwork and not becoming too ego-attached to my [code] babies. Respectful humor and helpfulness. </p>
	<p class="p-left">I cannot stress enough that a positive culture is more important in a workplace than the project. If offered a choice between enduring demoralizing backstabbing at a cool AI/robotics company, or being respectfully embraced by a kind work-family at a sanitation plant, choose the sanitation plant every time. And then earn your right to be there.</p>
